BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (Amara learned that the happiest she ever felt was NOT when she painted things for herself.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (It was when she saw a child eat a meal she'd painted, or a family sleep warm under a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (blanket she'd created.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (The joy of helping others was like a light inside her chest that never went out.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (Her selfish wishes had given her a moment of happiness. But her generous acts gave her a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (lifetime of it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td ('This is what the brush was teaching me all along,' she realized. 'My gift is not FOR me.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 592.2 Td (It's THROUGH me.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td ([Illustration: Amara watching children play in a schoolyard she painted, her hand over her) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td (heart, a glow of deep contentment and purpose, understanding her role as a giver]) Tj ET
