BT /F2 11 Tf 54 716.0 Td (Page 20) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (One evening, Amara sat painting a sunset on the hillside   just for the joy of it.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Her mother sat beside her. 'I remember when you only painted for yourself,' her mother) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (said.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td ('I'm glad I stopped,' Amara replied. 'Painting for myself made me feel full for a moment.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (But painting for others fills me up forever.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td ('That's because gifts are like seeds,' her mother said. 'When you plant them in others,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (they grow into something much bigger than what you started with.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 582.4 Td ([Illustration: Amara and her mother sitting on a hillside at sunset, Amara painting the) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td (real sunset with her glowing brush, a peaceful reflective scene of contentment and wisdom]) Tj ET
