BT /F2 11 Tf 54 716.0 Td (Page 23) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (Now, dear reader, here's what Amara wants you to know:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (You may not have a magic paintbrush, but you DO have gifts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (Maybe you're good at sports, or math, or making people laugh, or being a good listener, or) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (drawing, or building things.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (Whatever your gift is   it works the same way as Amara's brush.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (Use it to help others, and it will grow stronger and bring you more joy than you can) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (imagine. Keep it only for yourself, and it slowly fades away.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 582.4 Td ([Illustration: A child looking at their own hands, realizing their hands hold invisible) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td (gifts, a warm glow emanating from them, inspired by Amara's story to use their talents for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td (good]) Tj ET
endstream
